## Dynamic Provisioning, Metrics, and Backups

The <%= vars.platform_name %> Services SDK is designed to help you build enterprise-ready service offerings for the Marketplace. 
The SDK includes the following components:

* The [On Demand Service Broker](https://docs.pivotal.io/on-demand-service-broker) enables dynamic provisioning of your service using BOSH 2.0.

* [Service Metrics for <%= vars.platform_name %>](https://docs.pivotal.io/service-metrics) integrates your service into the <%= vars.platform_name %> Logging and Metrics system, empowering platform operators to gain immediate insight into system health based on live service metrics.

* [Service Backups for <%= vars.platform_name %>](https://docs.pivotal.io/service-backup/) runs regular backups for your service, triggering and uploading backup artifacts to a range of destinations, including S3 and Azure.

Active Pivotal partners and customers can use the <%= vars.platform_name %> Services SDK by agreeing to the Pivotal SDK EULA when downloading the products on  [https://network.pivotal.io/](https://network.pivotal.io/).
